This paper deals with the problem of generalization in neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning. The paper discusses various factors that affect the generalization ability of neural networks, such as the number of hidden layers, activation functions, and data representation. These factors are all relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on the generalization of neural networks, cs.LG and cs.NE are the most likely sub-categories.
